---
/*
  AiReadyClosing — short prose section on /solutions/ai-ready-content.

  Sequenced after the five AI-use-case chapter-blocks, before the CTA.
  Lands the 85% RAG retrieval precision metric — AI-Ready's homepage-
  canonical anchor per design brief §5 — as the closing punchline of
  paragraph 3 in primary text color (parallel to TDP's 72% and
  Migration's 45%).

  Layout (mirrors the closing sections on TDP / Migration / Interop)
    - container-prose width (~720 px), left-aligned
    - eyebrow + heading + three short body paragraphs
    - hairline top + bottom borders, 58 px symmetric padding (the
      tuned value from TDP / Migration / Interop)

  Animation: viewport-triggered fade-up. :nth-of-type indices are
  shifted by 1 because the eyebrow is the first <p>, so the first body
  paragraph is <p>:nth-of-type(2). prefers-reduced-motion: static.
*/
---

<section class="airdy-closing" aria-labelledby="airdy-closing-heading">
  <div class="container-prose airdy-closing__inner">
    <p class="eyebrow airdy-closing__eyebrow">The payoff</p>
    <h2 id="airdy-closing-heading" class="airdy-closing__heading">
      The measurement is the deliverable.
    </h2>
    <p class="airdy-closing__body">
      Precision isn&rsquo;t a number that comes out of the model. It comes out of a test harness. A replay corpus of real user queries &mdash; the same ones that produced the baseline &mdash; runs again after the structured content is in place, scored against ground-truth answers, with the same vector store and the same retrieval prompt.
    </p>
    <p class="airdy-closing__body">
      The same engineering pays compounding dividends. The corpus you build for chatbot retrieval is the same corpus that feeds semantic search, AI translation, fine-tuning, and compliance auditing. Five consumers, one substrate &mdash; every correction propagates everywhere.
    </p>
    <p class="airdy-closing__body airdy-closing__body--punch">
      On typical Extense engagements, RAG retrieval precision rises from a 25&ndash;35% baseline to 85%+ &mdash; measured against real user queries before the engagement closes. The number isn&rsquo;t promised. It&rsquo;s the deliverable.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .airdy-closing {
    /* Symmetric 58 px top/bottom padding so the hairlines bracket the
       content with equal breathing room — same treatment as TDP,
       Migration, and Interop closings. */
    padding-top: 58px;
    padding-bottom: 58px;
    border-top: var(--border-hairline);
    border-bottom: var(--border-hairline);
  }

  .airdy-closing__eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6) 0;
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
  }

  .airdy-closing__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-display-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8) 0;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .airdy-closing__body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6) 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .airdy-closing__body:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* The 85% punchline paragraph reads slightly heavier — same body
     type, but in primary color so the metric lands without becoming a
     stat block or stepping on the single-semantic-accent rule. */
  .airdy-closing__body--punch {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  /* Reveal animation. :nth-of-type indices shifted by 1 because the
     eyebrow is the first <p>. */
  .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__eyebrow,
  .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__heading,
  .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__body {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
  }

  .airdy-closing.animating.in-view .airdy-closing__eyebrow {
    animation: airdy-closing-fade-in 420ms ease-out forwards;
  }
  .airdy-closing.animating.in-view .airdy-closing__heading {
    animation: airdy-closing-fade-in 520ms ease-out forwards;
    animation-delay: 120ms;
  }
  .airdy-closing.animating.in-view .airdy-closing__body:nth-of-type(2) {
    animation: airdy-closing-fade-in 420ms ease-out forwards;
    animation-delay: 280ms;
  }
  .airdy-closing.animating.in-view .airdy-closing__body:nth-of-type(3) {
    animation: airdy-closing-fade-in 420ms ease-out forwards;
    animation-delay: 400ms;
  }
  .airdy-closing.animating.in-view .airdy-closing__body:nth-of-type(4) {
    animation: airdy-closing-fade-in 420ms ease-out forwards;
    animation-delay: 520ms;
  }

  @keyframes airdy-closing-fade-in {
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__eyebrow,
    .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__heading,
    .airdy-closing.animating .airdy-closing__body {
      opacity: 1 !important;
      transform: none !important;
      animation: none !important;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  function setupAiReadyClosing() {
    const sec = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(".airdy-closing");
    if (!sec) return;
    if (sec.dataset.closingRevealInit === "true") return;
    sec.dataset.closingRevealInit = "true";

    const prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia(
      "(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)"
    ).matches;
    if (prefersReducedMotion) return;

    sec.classList.add("animating");

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        entries.forEach((entry) => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            sec.classList.add("in-view");
            observer.unobserve(entry.target);
          }
        });
      },
      { threshold: 0.15 }
    );

    observer.observe(sec);
  }

  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", setupAiReadyClosing);
  document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", setupAiReadyClosing);
</script>
